tspan.tspan: Sensitivity vs. errors for homolog detection on the SCOP40 benchmark.

text.tspan: X axis is sensitivity as fraction of all homologs found above the threshold.
Y axis is false positive errors per query (FPEPQ).
At a given error rate, Reseek has substantially higher sensitivity than DALI,
Foldseek and TM-align. Inset is reported E-value vs. FPEPQ. Reseek E-values
are in good agreement with measured error rates, while Foldseek E-values are
underestimated. At Foldseek E-value threshold 1E-6 (circled), the measured
FPEPQ is ~0.1, i.e. five orders of magnitude higher than predicted.
